:'''Fizz:''' Tamila? You mean the musical actress?
:'''Fizz:''' Sorry, I'm not into musicals and don't know any celebs. However, she certainly made an impression on me...
:'''Fizz:''' Some time back, she kept coming over to ask if there was any novel similar to ''Evening Ember at the Goethe Hotel''.
:'''Fizz:''' I even read this book so I could make some suggestions for her... It's an excerpt from an unfinished romance novel.
:'''Fizz:''' She said that she loves this book, and I still remember how she said it. "It's such a blessing to read this book over and over again in a cozy warm bedroom with my flowers."
:'''Fizz:''' Unfortunately, the few books I recommended to her, she doesn't seem to be satisfied with them.
:'''Fizz:''' But that's pretty common... At some point, everyone finds that one book that is irreplaceable. Sometimes it has nothing to do with the book, but rather the reader's state of mind.
:'''Fizz:''' If there's nothing else, I'll get back to my book. See you later.
